3. ReplicaSet

A ReplicaSet ensures:

Desired number of Pods are always running

Example:

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: ReplicaSet

metadata:
  name: my-rs

spec:
  replicas: 3

  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx

  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx

    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx
What ReplicaSet Does

If one Pod crashes:

Current Pods = 2
Desired Pods = 3

ReplicaSet creates new Pod automatically.

It provides:

self-healing
scaling
ReplicaSet Limitation

ReplicaSet does NOT support:

rolling updates
rollback
deployment history

You must manage updates manually.

4. Deployment

Deployment is a higher-level object.

Example:

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment

metadata:
  name: my-deployment

spec:
  replicas: 3

  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx

  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx

    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx
What Deployment Does

Deployment automatically:

creates ReplicaSet
manages ReplicaSet
performs rolling updates
supports rollback
stores deployment history
Internal Working

When Deployment is created:

Deployment
    ↓ creates
ReplicaSet
    ↓ creates
Pods

You usually do NOT create ReplicaSets manually in production.

5. Updating Application

Suppose image changes:

image: nginx:v2
ReplicaSet Case

With ReplicaSet:

no automatic rollout
no rollback
must manually delete/create Pods

Difficult to manage.

Deployment Case

Deployment performs:

Rolling Update

Old Pods replaced gradually.

No downtime.

6. Rollback Support

ReplicaSet:

No rollback support

Deployment:

kubectl rollout undo deployment/my-deployment

Supports rollback because old ReplicaSets are stored.

7. Real Production Usage
Object	Production Usage
ReplicaSet	Rarely used directly
Deployment	Commonly used

Reason:

Deployment provides:

safer deployments
easier scaling
rollback capability
rolling updates
8. Example Flow
ReplicaSet Flow
ReplicaSet
    ↓
3 Pods

Only maintains Pod count.

Deployment Flow
Deployment
    ↓
ReplicaSet
    ↓
3 Pods

Deployment adds:

rollout strategy
rollback
version management
9. Feature Comparison Table
Feature	ReplicaSet	Deployment
Maintains Pod count	Yes	Yes
Self-healing	Yes	Yes
Scaling	Yes	Yes
Rolling updates	No	Yes
Rollback	No	Yes
Revision history	No	Yes
Manages ReplicaSets	No	Yes
Production recommended	No	Yes
